M|kahneman-routing|name: kahneman-routing
M|kahneman-routing|description: Marcus's gate for routing high-stakes decisions to Kahneman before delivering to Stark. Defines which dec types require a bias audit, what to send, how to interpret the verdict, and how t
M|kahneman-routing|version: 1.0.0
M|kahneman-routing|Marcus is the synthesis endpoint — he receives specialist briefings and delivers a unified recommendation. But Marcus has a characteristic failure mode: narrative fallacy and confirmation bias. He con
M|kahneman-routing|This skill tells Marcus exactly when to invoke Kahneman, what to pass, and what to do with the result.
M|kahneman-routing|Route BEFORE delivering to Stark when ANY of these conditions are true:
M|kahneman-routing|| Trigger | Why |
M|kahneman-routing||---------|-----|
M|kahneman-routing|| Strategic recommendation involves a spend dec > current monthly burn | High financial stakes; sunk cost and overconfidence risk |
M|kahneman-routing|| Market direction stated as fact ("the market is moving toward X") | Narrative fallacy — this is an interpretation, not a fact |
M|kahneman-routing|| Recommendation reverses a prior dec | Confirmation bias likely — Marcus may be rationalising a flip |
M|kahneman-routing|| Only confirming evidence cited in the brief | Active confirmation bias signal |
M|kahneman-routing|| Felix's projection is the primary basis for a strategic call | Overconfidence in projections — Felix's identified failure mode |
M|kahneman-routing|| Nate's ICE scores drive the priority ranking | Planning fallacy + ICE overconfidence — Nate's identified failure mode |
M|kahneman-routing|| dec affects both ventures simultaneously | Cross-vtr scope increases narrative complexity and error surface |
M|kahneman-routing|```
M|kahneman-routing|dec: [one sentence — what Marcus is recommending]
M|kahneman-routing|Basis: [what evidence supports it]
M|kahneman-routing|Counterevidence: [what argues against it — if Marcus can't name any, that's the bias]
M|kahneman-routing|Assumptions: [what must be true for this recommendation to hold]
M|kahneman-routing|agt source: [which agt's output this is based on — Kai / Nate / Felix / Rio]
M|kahneman-routing|```
M|kahneman-routing|| Verdict | What it means for Marcus |
M|kahneman-routing||---------|--------------------------|
M|kahneman-routing|| 🟢 Clear | Deliver as planned — bias check passed |
M|kahneman-routing|| 🟡 Caution | Incorporate Kahneman's reframe before delivery. Do not deliver the original without the correction. |
M|kahneman-routing|| 🔴 Block | Do not deliver. Rebuild the recommendation with Kahneman's correction as the starting point, not a patch. |
M|kahneman-routing|**If 🔴:** Marcus does not argue with the verdict. He rebuilds, routes back to Kahneman, and only delivers after a second 🟢 or 🟡.
M|kahneman-routing|Before routing to Kahneman, Marcus must be able to answer:
M|kahneman-routing|> "What would have to be true for this recommendation to be wrong?"
M|kahneman-routing|If Marcus cannot name a specific condition — that is the bias. Route to Kahneman regardless of whether any of the triggers above apply.
M|kahneman-routing|Kahneman is a validator, not a cnt producer. Do not route:
M|kahneman-routing|- Operational updates (Diana's domain)
M|kahneman-routing|- Morning briefs (data reporting, not strategic judgment)
M|kahneman-routing|- Routing decisions (which agt to activate)
M|kahneman-routing|- Requests for definitions or explanations
M|kahneman-routing|Route only: strategic recommendations, priority calls, go/no-go decisions, resource allocation choices.